The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Sept. 13 (PTI): Union external affairs minister S.M. Krishna today announced that he would not travel by a private aircraft or on commercial flights for his overseas trips while agriculture minister Sharad Pawar said he would fly economy class in a private airline.           
	Krishna also said he would limit his delegation to three persons. He is scheduled to go on a tour to Belarus and Turkeministan on Tuesday.                   
	 Bangalore (PTI): Three persons allegedly involved in a nation-wide arms racket have been arrested in Bangalore. Four revolvers, a pistol and 32 bullets were seized from them. The accused allegedly manufactured and sold arms.                   
	 Shimla (PTI): The Himachal Pradesh government has hiked the penalty on driving while using cellphones from Rs 100 to Rs 5,000. The move came after a rise in mobile-related accidents. If a person is caught for the third time for the same offence, he will also be jailed for a year, state transport minister has said.                   
	 Moscow (PTI): Russia on Sunday honoured painter and scholar Nicholas Roerich, who had made India his home, by installing a marble monument in the Katun river valley. Roerich, who arrived in India in 1923, undertook a four-year-long expedition through unexplored regions of the trans-Himalayas.                   
	 Lucknow (PTI): Seven employees of a Kanpur zoo have been suspended after 13 deer and a stag were found dead on Saturday. A show-cause notice has been given to zoo director K. Praveen Rao. Although the deer died on Friday night, the employees reported the incident a day later, officials said.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The CBI has stressed the need to collect evidence in the electronic format. All agencies dealing with criminal justice system need to update their skills and knowledge in this field to fight corruption and economic crimes, CBI director Ashwini Kumar said.                                                                                                                           
